torque-ameliorators 
  Ruby scripts that interrogate Torque to report state of the cluster

The command "see" provides an easy way to find other commands.

see
  processor-cores
  violations
  nodes
  users
  queue

Examples:
  see p
  see v
  see n
  see u
  see q


"see violations" is currently the only command that relies on ssh'ing into all of the nodes
via the "on-all-nodes-run" command


DEPENDENCIES:

 - Torque
 - Ruby
 - Ruby library (for "on-all-nodes-run" and indirectly "see violations"): open3 
